CD- Continuous Delivery / Continuous Deployment:
------------------------------------------------
CI - build + test
CD - Deploy


Continuous Delivery vs Continuous Deployment:
---------------------------------------------

	1. Continuous Delivery (manual approval required):

		- developer pushes code
		- jenkins builds & tests
		- code goes to dev - qa
		- before production:
			manual approval needed (Client / QA sign-off)
		- then you manually trigger deployment

		keypoint: deployment is automated, but trigger is manual

		Example:
		---------
		QA team says: All tests passed
		Client gives aproval
		You got to jenins and click 'Build/Deploy' manually


	2. Continuous Deployment (Fully Automated):

		- developer pushes code
		- jenkins:
			build, test, deploy to dev - qa - prod automatically

		keypoint: everything is automated end-to-end

		Example:
		---------
		code pushed, tests passed, automatically goes to production (ho human intervention)


Internal vs External Porjects (Important Insight):
--------------------------------------------------
External projects (Clients like Facebook, Banking apps) -> Use Continuous Delivery:

	Reason:
		- need client approval
		- cannot directly push to production


Internal Projects (HRMS, Payroll): Use Continuous Deployment:

	Reason:
		- used inside compnay
		- no strict approval needed
		- faster releases


Final Simple Summary:
=====================
CI - build + test automatically
Continuous Delivery - Manual approval before production
Continuous Deployment - Fully automatic deployment
External apps - Delivery
Internal apps - Deployment
